      "content": "that's exactly what they want u to think though. they use stuff like \"compression artifacts\" or \"mixing choices\" as cover so nobody questions it. if someone wanted to influence a population, they wouldn't use an obvious siren, they'd use something hidden in the music that bypasses the conscious mind. if it's possible to hide data in images or text, why wouldn't it be possible to hide psychoacoustic triggers in an audio stream? i need practical ways to protect myself, like how do i identify if a frequency is being used to manipulate my mood?",
